The paper also mentions the lack of training data and computing power, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the applications of convolutional neural networks in natural language processing, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions achieving state-of-the-art results, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
